Rub the inside of the fondue pot vigorously with the garlic halves. Add the wine, peppercorns, thyme and bay leaf to the pot and bring to the boil.Toss the cheeses in a bowl with the cornflour. Lower the heat and gradually stir in the cheeses, a handful at a time, until melted. Keep stirring constantly.Simmer gently until the mixture is smooth and glossy, taking care not to let the fondue burn or boil. Stir in the grappa and keep the fondue warm while serving.To serve, arrange the accompaniments on a large platter and use fondue prongs to dip these into the pot.